(162, 0, '2024-04', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'CST HUB: A WEB-BASED APPLICATION SYSTEM FOR STYLE FORMATTING ANALYSIS OF UMAK CS THESIS MANUSCRIPT USING COMPOSITE RULE-BASED ALGORITHM', 'MHIKE LAURENCE N. LACONSAY-HENSON S. BUNAYOG-RAPHAEL JORREL H. DOCOT-CHASTINE JOY B. SANQUI-AIA A. VALLES', '', 'This study focuses on developing a system for style formatting analysis of UMak CS Thesis Manuscripts using Composite Rule-Based Algorithm by utilizing Python Libraries such as PyMuPDF, and Tesseract OCR. The system consists of calculating bounding boxes to check the formatting of CS thesis papers, providing a valuable tool for students and professors to efficiently review and reduce formatting errors. The method involves calculating PDF paper size, margins, spacings and defining fonts. Using Tesseract OCR and PyMuPDF, the system extracts text details, detects margins, and calculates text spacings. The model detects the errors by highlighting them with OpenCV specifically fonts, margins, and spacing. Despite difficulties in manual data extraction and time-consuming margin and spacing detection, the developed system proves useful in improving UMak CS Thesis Manuscript formatting, resulting with an overall accuracy rate of 90.66% across various formatting components specifically: margin, spacings, and font-related, with a potential for future refinements. Furthermore, the system evaluation reached an overall rating of 3.55, indicating a general acceptance among Computer Science (CS) students and professors.', 'Style Formatting Analysis, Formatting Errors, Composite Rule-based Algorithm, UMak CS Thesis Manuscripts, Text Extraction, Data extraction.'),
(163, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A PROPOSED NETWORK SECURITY FOR MARB PRINTING SERVICES', 'ARANETA, JAN LORRY F. - BUENAOBRA, KENNETH JR. I. - DELA VEGA, JOANNE R.', '', 'This study addresses the cybersecurity challenges faced by MARB Printing Services and proposes a network security to enhance protection against cyber threats. The objective is to propose a network security encompassing physical, network, and application security measures for the future expansion of the company. The methodology involves enhancing the existing network with Sophos XG Firewall, Sophos XG XDR, and an improved network layout. Utilizing Cisco devices like routers, switches, and network cabling, along with configuring firewalls, VLAN, RIP, TCP, and WAN, ensures security of critical and confidential information, maintaining the company\'s operational stability. Additionally, Windows Server 2022 is recommended for centealized user management and secure file storage. Results indicate that both IT professionals and employees, achieving a composite evaluation mean of 4.04, indicating strong agreement on its effectiveness. Key outcomes include better identification and mitigation of security flaws, enhanced data protection, and efficient traffic management. The continuous surveillance and proactive measures, such as regular alerts and training, contribute to building trust among clients and partners. Recommendations include designing for future expansion, collaborating with cybersecurity experts, adopting new technologies, and developing a comprehensive incident response plan to maintain and enhance security measures as the cybersecurity landscape evolves.This study serves ', 'Cybersecurity challenges, Network security, Physical security measures, Network security measures, Application security measure.'),
(164, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A PROPOSED OF SECURED WIDE AREA NETWORK USING IPSEC VIRTUAL PRIVATE NETWORK FOR ALPHA PLUS PROPERTY HOLDINGS CORPORATION', 'MARIYHELA DENNISE P. CHAN - BRYAN JOSHUA B. MANANSALA - MARK EDSON H. ROMARATE', '', 'The proposal focused on the enhancement of the network security of Alpha Plus Property Holdings Corporation by implementing a secured Wide Area Network (WAN) using IPsec Virtual Private Network (VPN) technology. The solution involves deploying IPsec VPN for site-to-site and remote access connections, integrating Fortinet security solutions and Google Workspace Business Plus for improved collaboration. The implementation plan includes comprehensive testing to ensure enhanced security, improved performance, and streamlined communication. The proposal aims to provide reliable network infrastructure tailored to the corporation\'s needs, by utilizing VMWare Workstation, Windows Server 2022, Fortinet FortiGate Firewall, and Cisco Packet Tracer. In compliance with ISO/IEC 27001 standards are emphasized to ensure information security and effective risk management, with the deployed network elements serving as crucial protectors of valuable data and enabling authorized access exclusively. The proposed solution will enhance threat detection and incident response, conduct security audits and vulnerability assessments, and improve the overall security and efficiency of Alpha Plus Property Holdings Corporation\'s network infrastructure, thereby reducing the risk of data breaches and cyber-attacks.', '(WAN) Wide area network, (IPsec VPN) Internet Protocol Security Virtual Private Network, (ISO/IEC 27001) international standard for information securi'),
(165, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A PROPOSED WAN INFRASTRUCTURE DESIGN USING AN ALTERNATIVE NEXT-GENERATION FIREWALL UTILIZING SD-WAN AND IPSEC VPN FOR NEW WORLD DIAGNOSTICS (NWD)', 'TOLOSA, ROD VINCE M. - BREGIAS, MARK JOHN M. - SIBAL, JASPER L.', '', 'This study examines an alternative next-generation firewall for New World Diagnostics which has the same features and functionalities such as SD-WAN and IPsec VPN, while being more economically viable and suitable to the needs of the organization. This study\'s topic arose as the organization\'s current next-generation firewall costs exceeded what the organization was comfortable with, therefore looking for another option. This study will be a testbed and a proposal for a new alternative next-generation firewall and a few tweaks and improvements to the current network design. Incorporating related literature and studies enabled the researchers to possess more insight, understanding, and knowledge in the undertaking of this study\'s completion. Simulations and tests were also done on the proposed network designs, particularly the local area network (LAN) and the wide area network (WAN) for basic functionalities such as VLANs and DHCP to more complex features such as SD-WAN and IPsec VPN. Finally, the proposed network design was evaluated by IT specialists and users from New World Diagnostics, this enabled the researchers to have a holistic evaluation and review of the proposal, and also support its integrity. This study\'s results proved that alternative next-generation firewalls suited the needs of organizations similar to New World Diagnostics with top-of-the-line features such as SD-WAN and IPsec VPN. Equipped with specifications that are much more in line with the size and nee', 'Network Infrastructure Design, Wide Area Network (WAN), Local Area Network (LAN), Software Defined Wide Area Network (SD-WAN), IPsec VPN, Next-Generat'),
(166, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A PROPOSED WEB APPLICATION WITH CLOUD-BASED SECURITY FOR INTEGRATIVE LEARNING CONTENT-BASED SYSTEM FOR SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS OF PRESIDENT DIOSDA', 'ORMIDO, JOHN MARK M. - PAZ, JHET CHRISTIAN V. - VIVO, SARAH ERICA D.', '', 'This paper helps you understand and know how to develop an online learning management system from the base with the cloud-based security that is reinforced for an additional layer of security for the system which can give peace of mind to the users of the developed project. With the help of the standards that we are utilizing and using nowadays such as AICC, SCORM, API, and cmi5, the developers successfully developed an online learning management system which is for President Diosdado Macapagal High School, this project is addressing the issues of the users of the President Diosdado Macapagal High School like missing requirements, not accurate recordings, missing paper works and many more. Based on the of the results and summary of findings that has the researchers gathered from testing and interviews, the performance efficiency, the PDMHS-LMS gets a weighted average mean of 4.21, compatibility testing also gets a staggering value of 4.2 weighted average mean. In terms of usability, the PDMHS-LMS has the weighted average mean of 4.31, lastly, reliability, reliability gets a 4.20 weighted average mean. In conclusion the proposed technology PDMHS-LMS is effective and reliable as an alternative solution for the existing problems that is in the President Diosdado Macapagal High School, with this and backed-up by the research results from the interview and research that the researchers performed.', 'Learning management system, cloud security, database, administrator, ISO 25010, modules, dashboard, web-based application, server, database, switches,'),
(167, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A WEB-BASED BARANGAY RESIDENT INFORMATION SYSTEM', 'ARAZA, ASHLEY TRAVIS - CATIG, CESAR B. JR. - TOBIAS, JAN EARL M.', '', 'In order to address the difficulty that has been affecting the barangay North Signal in Taguig City, the goal of this study is to offer a solution. The strategy involved developing a digital information system for the barangay to serve as a tool for addressing manual processes. A web-based system known as the Barangay Information System is equipped with functionalities for storing, processing, generating, and managing resident\'s information. The system ensures the security of the system through the implementation of authorization, employing a one-time password (OTP) for additional layer of security to authenticate users during login, ensuring that only the legitimate account holder can perform actions or access sensitive information. Information was properly protected utilizing encryption, decryption and data backup mechanisms, including reCAPTCHA for validating users distinguishing between bots and humans. To develop an information management system, the proponents utilized the PHP programming language. Furthermore, this generate an online backup of the user\'s information to maintain data integrity that assures the information of the users are stored securely within the system. This significantly optimize the management of residence documents and information for Barangay North Signal residents. The research acknowledged that the system has limitations, such as security in biometrics, online transactions, and chatbot. Overall, the research indicates that implementing a web-ba', 'Resident Information System, Web-based, PHP, reCAPTCHA, OneTime Password, Encryption and Decryption, Backup, Digital, North Signal, Taguig City.'),
(168, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'ASIAN HOSPITAL HEALTH DATA HUB: DEVELOPMENT OF RESEARCH INFORMATION SYSTEM FOR ASIAN HOSPITAL', 'BUENO, REVIN R. - GENERAO, JONAS G. - MEJILLANO, BEA BIANCA R.', '', 'The Hospital Research Information System is a web-based software application tailored for Asian Hospital aimed at modernizing and enhancing the research process within the institution. The Hospital Research Information System aims to digitize and optimize research workflows within Asian Hospital. By leveraging technology, the hospital aims to overcome challenges associated with manual processes. The research design for developing a research information system for Asian Hospital adopts a descriptive approach to address its research process challenges. The study begins with an introduction outlining the need for Enhanced effectiveness and optimized user satisfaction in the research process. A literature review explores successful implementations and challenges faced by similar systems in research settings providing insights to inform the de development process. The study evaluated the web systems functionality, reliability, usability, and security and the results showed that the web system has excellent performance and usability and is reliable and secure. Results of testing reveal that research is reliably recorded and kept in the database and the website is compatible with a range of devices and browsers assuring easy accessibility and operation. And lastly, the results of the evaluation that the Asian Hospital Health Data Hub has been effective in addressing the demands of Asian Hospital needs.', 'Hospital Research Information System, Asian Hospital Health Data Hub'),
(169, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'DESIGNING A SCALABLE AND FLEXIBLE NETWORK ARCHITECTURE FOR MANDALUYONG COLLEGE OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY WITH INTER-VLAN ROUTING AND ETHERCHANNEL BUND', 'BUSTILLO, PAUL NATHAN P. - CHUA, JULIUS S. - ROCHA, NATHANIEL GLENN M.', '', 'As digital technologies rapidly expand, educational institutions must innovate with strong network infrastructures to support diverse academic and administrative activities. This capstone project addresses the unique challenges faced by Mandalyong College of Science and Technology (MCST), a new institution with a direct internet connection.    This network setup makes MCST vulnerable to cyberattacks and unreliable internet connections. To address these issues, the researchers proposed a comprehensive network architecture to enhance MCST\'s connectivity, redundancy, scalability, and security. The project focuses on developing a scalable and flexible network infrastructure integrating Inter-VLAN Routing and    EtherChannel Bundling Technology, aiming to establish a resilient and adaptable network for current and future needs. Key objectives include optimizing the local area network, vast area network, server management, and network security using tools like Cisco Packet Tracer and GNS3, aligning with ISO 27001:2022 standards. The study used a Likert Scale to evaluate Organizational Control, Physical Control, Technological Control, Redundancy, Scalability, and Reliability, yielding positive results from evaluators. Successful testing validated the proposed project\'s functionality and reliability. This project enhances MCST\'s network infrastructure, providing practical insights and methodologies for newly established institutions. It lays a resilient foundation for the future grow', 'Digital Technology, Network Infrastructure, Cyberattacks, Redundancy, Scalability, Inter-VLAN Routing, EtherChannel Bundling, Digital technologies'),
(170, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'DEVELOPING AN ONLINE ADMISSION SYSTEM FOR MANDALUYONG COLLEGE OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY', 'BALBUENA, RON ALVIN O. - LAMADORA, MICHELLE IRISH L. - ROC, ROSELYN F.', '', 'Online Admission System is a web-based software application that helps to automate and simplify the process of admitting students into educational institutions such as schools, colleges, and universities. Mandalyong College of Science and Technology is a newly opened educational institution located in Mandalyong City, Philippines. This school currently carries out the admissions process manually and faces challenges managing the increasing number of applicants using Google Forms, which raises concerns about data security and privacy. This study aims to develop an Online Admission System for Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology to replace the traditionally manual process of admission, which can be time-consuming, prone to errors and lacks adequate security measures. The proposed system offers a secure and user-friendly online admission system with features such as content management, data analytics, and two-factor authentication. This system can help the school automate administrative tasks related to admissions, such as managing applications and applicant data.The method used in this study is Agile Methodology. This method is popular in the IT industry known for its adaptability and flexibility in responding to user needs.The evaluation results showed strong agreement with 83.33% rating the system\'s accuracy, ease of use, reliability, and security in managing applications and applicant data. The findings showed that the researchers successfully developed an online ad', 'Admission System, Online Admission System, Online Examination System'),
(171, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'DEVELOPING AN ONLINE REGISTRATION SYSTEM FOR MANDALUYONG COLLEGE OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY', 'DACUYCUY, JOSEPH WILLIAM G. - DORONILA, DENISE CLAIRE B.', '', 'Online Registration System is a web-based software application that helps to automate and simplify the process of admitting students into educational institutions such as schools, colleges, and universities. Mandalyong College of Science and Technology is a newly opened educational institution located in Mandaluyong City, Philippines. This school currently carries out the admissions process manually and faces challenges managing the increasing number of applicants using Google Forms, which raises concerns about data security and privacy. This study aims to develop an Online Registration System for Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology to replace the traditional manual process of registration, and lessen the use load of papers which can be time-consuming, prone to errors, and lack adequate security measures. The proposed system offers a secure and user-friendly online registration system with features such as management of contents for administrators, registrar, and end-users for students. This system can help the school automate tasks related to registration, such as managing applications and applicant data. The method used in this study is Agile Methodology. This method is popular in the IT industry known for its adaptability and flexibility in responding to user needs. The evaluation results showed strong agreement with \"4.02 over 5\" rating the system\'s accuracy, functionality, performance efficiency, compatibility, usability, reliability, security, maintainability,', 'Online Registration System, Mandalyong College of Science and Technology, Admissions, Registration, Agile Methodology, Authenticated'),
(172, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'DEVELOPMENT OF A WEB-BASED SEXUALITY EDUCATION PLATFORM FOR ADOLESCENTS', 'BENITEZ, TRIXIE MAY C. - GARCIA, JAHMEL ANDRE C. - GRAMATICA, JULIUS A.', '', 'This paper explores the development and evaluation of a web-based platform for sexuality education, aimed at addressing the lack of comprehensive sexuality education materials in educational institutions. Chapter 1 delves into the background of the issue, highlighting the challenges faced in implementing comprehensive sexuality education in the Philippines. Chapter 2 reviews related literature, providing insights from various studies on sexuality education, online resources, and the effectiveness of web-based programs. In Chapter 5, the study\'s findings, conclusions, and recommendations are presented. The findings indicate that the developed web-based platform performed well in terms of performance efficiency, usability, security, functionality, and maintainability, as evaluated based on ISO 25010 standards. Conclusions drawn from the study emphasize the importance of web-based tools in delivering comprehensive sexuality education and the need for continuous improvement in such platforms. Recommendations include adding a summative test and implementing a certification system to enhance student learning and engagement. Overall, this study contributes to addressing the challenges in providing comprehensive sexuality education through innovative technological solutions.', 'Web-based Sexuality Education, Sexuality Education Platform, Learning Management System');
